Title: Fusion rules in conformal field theory

Authors: J. Fuchs

Comments: 68 pages, LaTeX. changed contents of footnote no. 9

Journal-ref: Fortsch.Phys. 42 (1994) 1-48

Several aspects of fusion rings and fusion rule algebras, and of theirdiagonalization and the connection with modular invariance; the presentation interms of quotients of polynomial rings; fusion graphs; various strategies thatallow for a partial classification; and the role of the fusion rules in theconformal bootstrap programme.